data.title: Brunch
data.text: The Generator is a coffee shop complete with gourmet blends of coffees and teas.  They also serve a nice brunch and usually have musical entertainment playing while you eat which play for tips.  On Sunday's, they usually have a good crowd, but I've never had a long wait.  Menu includes from breakfast items such as omlettes, eggs Benedict, crepes, waffles, and quiche.  They also serve sandwhiches and have homemade deserts.  The tortilla soup is delicious, but a little bit spicy if you don't eat more than mild picante sauce.  Lastly, the place is very quaint and homey, so people are hanging around just listening to music, playing games, crocheting, and using wifi.

data.title: New Mgmt Changes
data.text: This is a charming coffee shop in down town Garland.  It was perfect and new owners have to make their mark.  The new bright white sub way tile does not fit the decor of the building.  What were you thinking?  We invited another couple to lunch and we could not hear each other talk the music was so loud.  We have loved the harpist and piano players for lunch but these two musicians didn't realize this is a small restaurant, you don't need to scream.  The food was good but now no salad and the tea glass is half the size it used to be.  Are they cutting back to save money?

data.title: New setup
data.text: Don't care for new setup....no breakfast except weekends. Did like eggs on China instead of paper and plastic. Warm and personable entrepreneur full of charm.

data.title: Nice Find in Downtown Garland
data.text: Recently re-found this place and think it has a new owner.  Had liked it when I'd been there before, but even more impressed this time on a Sunday.  Offering brunch and even though they'd run out of what I wanted, my second choice of a vegetable omelette was excellent.  The free mimosa is a nice touch and the live music, too.  Very nice atmosphere and even though service was a little slow it was fine.  Was there with a group and we had plenty to talk about while we waited.  Owner was very friendly and hands on working his tail off to make sure everything was good.  I will definitely keep this place in mind for future meals out.  Loving that downtown Garland is growing in the restaurant scene.  Yea!!

data.title: Stress free ordering
data.text:
I walked in and ordered my decaf latte 5 minutes before closing and the employee was sweet (female).  I asked if I could hang out for a few extra minutes and she did not mind.  After I sat down a few more customers came in and were also served with a smile.  By that time it was already after closing time.  Very impressive
My coffee with almond milk was very smoothe.

data.title: Great Place to have coffee or a meal!
data.text: Great atmosphere, good coffee, tea and food, good value.  I love the character of this old building.  It is charming and comfortable.  This is a great place to go to meet with friends, have a drink or meal.  This would be a great place as a mobile office to get out of the house.

data.title: Generator worth a stop
data.text: Nir and his team at Generator could not have been more friendly and the atmosphere was lovely with the exposed brick, cool art and acoustic guitarist playing up front. Oh and did we mention the coffee is fantastic, too? When you don't have to add sugar that tells you something. We arrived simply to stop in and check it out but were met with a kind, complimentary mimosa. We also were treated to a delicious scone and snickerdoodle before we left. Truly a testament to the commitment Nir is making with his home on the Garland Square. We understand wine is coming soon?! This is worth a drive over from wherever you live

data.title: Great space, decent coffee, slow service
data.text: Cool looking spot in the historic downtown. Service was lacking, fairly indifferent greeting when we came in. Coffee and food was slow to come out. Took about 5 minutes to get a piece of quiche. Seriously? All you have to do is cut it and maybe heat it up for half a minute in the microwave. The place was NOT at ALL crowded. They forgot silverware for the first two breakfasts in our group (of 3). Couldn't figure out how it stays open if that's what their service ethic is about. Could be so much more.

data.title: Unsupervised Children
data.text: What's up with the unsupervised children?  The last two times I have eaten lunch here there are 3 or 4 children playing and hanging out on the couch.  These  children seem to be unsupervised as they never approach and adults at a table and no adults come to them.  Are these the employees children? Last Saturday when we left the two boys were playing chase !  We love the food, coffee and music.  We don't love the kids running around.  Don't get me wrong.  I love kids.  I just think children under 10 years old need an adult's eye on them.

data.title: Never dissappointed.
data.text: Great coffee, food and atmosphere.  Never been disappointed.  Food service is slow but the food is good.  Always enjoy the live music.  One of my husbands favorite places in Garland.

data.title: Suprising
data.text: Cute coffee house and great Chi Tea Latte.  Fun atmosphere, there was a girl singing and every table was full.  The drinks were great and the staff very friendly.  The wait time for our drinks however, was way too long!  We ordered 2 teas, 2 hot chocolates and 1 regular coffee and we waited a little over 20 minutes, and others ahead of us waited as long too.  If they could do something about the wait time, I think I would like to go back.

data.title: Great stopping place on the square
data.text: Must go here when in Garland. Good coffee and AMAZING desserts. Super comfy place all around. Their breakfast platter is reasonable and really good. Quiche amazing.

data.title: great pie
data.text: nice coffee shop on the square great desserts and atmosphere, nice place to relax and one the best coconut cream pies I have ever had

data.title: Nice place slow service
data.text: Walked in and the atmosphere was great. I ordered a sandwich and a drink and waited about 20 minutes to be served. There were about 2 orders ahead of me. The food was ok and the drink was good,but the service was very slow. If you have the time to wait it's not bad.

data.title: Casual and Easy
data.text:
I met a friend for an early lunch. She had the quiche and I had the chicken salad sandwich. Both were very good. I love chicken salad with grapes in it. The croissant it was on was very buttery. 
The staff members were pleasant, chatty, and helpful. There was a Fun Run going on right across the street and the shop had been very busy before we came in, but the staff was laughing about how they handled it. 
It's very laid back and casual. There was one table with people playing cards. My friend and I sat outside. I would certainly go back.

data.title: Okay Coffee Shop
data.text: Walked in and waited to be seated.  After a minute we realized it was "Seat yourself".  No wait staff, you go to a counter to order.  Food choices are quite limited.  I had the Breakfast Plate (2 eggs, bacon and toast) and my wife had a chicken salad sandwich.  They were actually pretty good. The really bad part was the live music.  Just inside the door was a guy with an electric guitar.  I guess some people may enjoy his voice.  We didn't.  He and the guitar were both WAY TOO LOUD.  We really couldn't even hold a conversation.  When I place our order, I had to ask the counter person to repeat everything.l  The inside is brick and wood, making the acoustics not suitable for any type of music.  Because of the loud music and very limited menu I doubt we will be back.

data.title: Very comfortable feel
data.text: The Generator is one of my favorite places to sit and chill. They have a very relaxed and comfy space. Coffee is good and food is WONDERFUL. Try the pastries they are amazing. They also have quite a few live music nights and it is nice to just sit and listen. If you are in town you should check them out!

data.title: Coffee shop & bakery
data.text: The best coffee house in Garland.  Today's lunch was an incredible tortilla soup and a raspberry petit four for dessert and both were incredible.  Also try the panini's.  Everything from bakery has been great

data.title: Full of Flavor
data.text:
I always try to seek out local coffee shops for my craving (Garland has NO others), and this one is adorable... exposed brick, old-style tin ceiling, antique in a steampunk meets art nouveau kind of way. I visited Garland for a few days, loved this place so much I came back a second time!

Tried it for brunch -- the spinach quiche was homemade and delicious! My friend had the egg croissant and said it was really good. My latte was legit (organic & fair-trade) and I couldn't resist trying the cookies, which were decadent -- especially the chocolate ones with the powdered sugar on top. I'd recommend brunch, coffee, or dessert -- apparently they are known for their pie.

They also showcase local artists and feature live music on the weekends. Everything about this place is wonderful - ambiance, food, coffee, desserts, service... definitely worth a stop!

data.title: Starbucks "WHO?"
data.text: Loveee this place! It is such a treat to have a great cafe with a personal touch still around. Their Southern Pecan coffee with warmed heavy cream and a warm blueberry scone..Wow.. And for lunch a grilled Swiss cheese sandwich with fresh spinach and tomatoes.. lookout Starbucks, you could learn from these people.
